text: Sint-Michielsgestel is a municipality in the Dutch province of North Brabant. In 2019, 28,991 people lived there. In its current composition, the municipality was created in 1996 by the merger of Sint-Michielsgestel, Den Dungen and Berlicum plus Gemonde, a population center consisting of four villages previously divided among the neighboring municipalities. == References == Category:Settlements in North Brabant Category:Municipalities of North Brabant
title: Sint-Michielsgestel
